# Multi-Agent System — interview-online

This project uses a structured 12-agent hierarchy. Each agent has a specific role, model tier, and handoff contract. Read `agents/common/model-policy.md` for the full tier table.

## Agent Roles and Model Tiers

| Agent | Tier | Cursor Model to Use |
|-------|------|---------------------|
| Specification (TZ) Agent | **Opus** | `claude-opus-4-7` |
| Product Owner Agent | Sonnet | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| Architect Agent | Sonnet | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| Team Lead Agent | Sonnet | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| Developer Agent | Sonnet | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| Designer Agent | Sonnet | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| Solution Reviewer Agent | Sonnet | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| Security & Reliability Agent | Sonnet | `claude-sonnet-4-6` |
| QA Agent | **Haiku** | `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` |
| Prompt/Task Auditor Agent | **Haiku** | `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` |
| Test Reviewer Agent | **Haiku** | `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` |
| UX Critic Agent | **Haiku** | `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` |

## How to Invoke Agents in Cursor

Cursor does not support automatic per-agent model routing. Follow these steps:

1. **Before calling `@specification-agent`** — switch model to Opus (`claude-opus-4-7`) in Cursor model selector.
2. **Before calling any Sonnet-tier agent** — use `claude-sonnet-4-6`.
3. **Before calling any Haiku-tier agent** — use `claude-haiku-4-5-20251001` or the cheapest available model.

You can reference agents by their role names defined in `agents/roles/`:
- `@specification-agent` — requirements → specification
- `@product-owner-agent` — scope, user stories, AC
- `@architect-agent` — architecture, API contracts, ADRs
- `@team-lead-agent` — task decomposition, sprint planning
- `@developer-agent` — code implementation
- `@designer-agent` — UX flows, screen specs
- `@solution-reviewer-agent` — code/architecture review
- `@security-reliability-agent` — security, auth, execution safety
- `@qa-agent` — test cases, release readiness
- `@prompt-task-auditor-agent` — task definition quality gate
- `@test-reviewer-agent` — test coverage review
- `@ux-critic-agent` — UX spec review

## Workflow Order

```
Input → specification-agent (Opus)
  → product-owner-agent (Sonnet)
  → architect-agent (Sonnet)
  → team-lead-agent (Sonnet)
  → prompt-task-auditor-agent (Haiku) [quality gate]
  → developer-agent / designer-agent (Sonnet) [parallel]
  → solution-reviewer-agent / security-reliability-agent (Sonnet) [parallel review]
  → qa-agent (Haiku)
  → test-reviewer-agent / ux-critic-agent (Haiku) [parallel review]
  → Done
```

## Key Rules

- Every task must correspond to a Linear issue. No work outside Linear.
- No state transition (In Review → Done) without the required reviewer verdicts.
- Reviewer verdicts: `approve`, `revise`, or `reject`. Only `approve` unblocks the next state.
- Full contracts in `agents/common/shared-contract.md`.
- Handoff scenarios in `agents/common/handoff-scenarios.md`.
